            "text": "Virginia panel DENIES consolidation of the four gun-ban suits — a procedural win for challengers",
            "wrap": true,
            "spacing": "Small"
          },
          {
            "type": "TextBlock",
            "text": "A three-judge panel refused to combine the four Virginia “assault firearms” ban lawsuits, so each proceeds in its own court. It’s a setback for AG Jay Jones’s defense — not a merits ruling — and the “muddled” enforcement picture is unchanged.",
            "wrap": true,
            "spacing": "Small"
